                                                                    liberalization in the 1990s. Indian companies
                                                                    have
                                                                    been attracting foreign investments and
                                                                    similarly,
                                                                    Indian companies have been making investments
                                                                    abroad. With the rapid advances in technology,
                                                                    new
                                                                    areas of business are emerging, and legal
                                                                    practitioners must keep pace with these emerging
                                                                    technologies to advise clients in the absence of
                                                                    regulations or underdeveloped regulations.<br>
                                                                    Further, to facilitate the movement of material,
                                                                    services, capital, technology, and human
                                                                    resources
                                                                    across borders, legal practitioners must equip
                                                                    themselves with the legal nuances involved in
                                                                    performing economic activities in a
                                                                    multilocational
                                                                    and geographical environment. Lawyers should be
                                                                    able
                                                                    to effectively advise on the legal and political
                                                                    advantages and disadvantages of investing in
                                                                    different countries. It requires knowledge of
                                                                    labor
                                                                    laws and practices, and commercial and tax laws
                                                                    in
                                                                    different countries. The demand for
                                                                    practitioners
                                                                    with domestic and international commercial law
                                                                    knowledge has been growing.
                                                                </p>
